node.text: Banana Stand Jams 2022!

Sister Maria Jose has a very special message for all of our asuCatholic students and community. She will be going back to Peru to finish her degree in Theology on December 30th.  We weren’t expecting to say goodbye so soon but we are so excited to see where her vocation takes her. Sister Maria Jose is a friend to many and a mentor to us all. She will be missed dearly and by many! She has made her mark here at ASU and the Newman Center and we are excited for her to finish her studies and build her relationship with the Lord. 
•
•
Thank you for all that you do for us at asuCatholic and we will be praying for you Sister! 
•
•
If you would like to say goodbye to Sister Maria Jose she is opening her home on Monday December 28th from 3-7pm. Please email her for her address if you do not have it already!! spdmariajose@asucatholic.org

node.text:
Our final @sponational missionary interview ft. Bernadette Prickel!

And if you want to find out more about Bernadette, make sure to check out the extended interview on our asuCatholic page. There, Bernadette gives insight to her journey as a missionary.

All new “Campus Ministry Staff Interview” ft. second-year @sponational missionary Luke Swanson!

And if you want to find out more about Luke, make sure to check out the extended interview on our asuCatholic page. There, Luke gives insight into his journey as a missionary.

Learn more about our new and first-time @sponational missionary Thomas Corzo in this new edition of “Campus Ministry Interviews”!

And if you want to find out more about Thomas, make sure to check the extended interview video on our asuCatholic YouTube page. There, Thomas shares his discernment into being a missionary and his upcoming mission at ASU. (link in bio)

In this round of “Campus Ministry Interviews”, we got to learn more about our wonderful @sponational missionary Kylie Larzelere!

And if you’re looking to get to know Kylie even better, check out the extended interview video on our asuCatholic YouTube page. There, we delve deeper into Kylie’s discernment into being a missionary and her work at ASU. (link in bio)

Get to know our campus minister Sister Maria José @spd_arizona a little more in this new edition of asuCatholic staff interviews!

And just like before, you can check out the extended version of the interview on our asuCatholic YouTube channel (link in bio). There, Sister Maria offers insight into her journey as a sister serving the community Servants of the Plan of God as well as her time spent here at Newman.

What better way to learn more about ASU Newman’s newest clergy member and campus minister @frcruzer than a fun, rapid-fire question interview?

And check out the extended edition of this interview on our asuCatholic YouTube page! In that video, we delve deeper into Fr. Daniel’s journey as a priest and his mission here at Newman. Link in bio

In case you missed it last night, here is our End of the Year slideshow! Thank you all once again for this great year and for being a part of this amazing community.
.
This video is also on our YouTube page asuCatholic along with other fun campus ministry-related memories and highlights. Feel free to check it out!
